  "prompt": "Is it possible to change names in savings a/c?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to change the name on a savings account, but the process and requirements can vary depending on the bank's policies. Generally, you'll need to:\n\n1. **Contact Your Bank:** Reach out to your bank's customer service or visit a local branch to initiate the name change request.\n\n2. **Provide Documentation:** Be prepared to provide legal documentation to support the name change, such as:\n   - A marriage certificate (if changing your name due to marriage)\n   - A divorce decree (if reverting to a previous name)\n   - A court order (for other legal name changes)\n   - Updated identification documents (such as a new driver\u2019s license or passport)\n\n3. **Fill Out Required Forms:** The bank might ask you to fill out specific forms to process the name change.\n\n4. **Update Associated Information:** Ensure that other information linked to your account, such as debit/credit cards, checks, and online banking profile, is also updated accordingly.\n\nAlways check with your particular bank for their specific procedures and any additional requirements they might have.",
